Description: GUI Linux security audit tool with everyday-language explanations
 Linux Security Dashboard is a PyQt6 desktop application that audits Linux
 security posture in everyday language. Designed for users who want to
 understand whether their system is safe without needing a cybersecurity
 background.
 .
 Features:
  * Everyday-language explanations of every finding
  * One-click guided fixes with confirmation dialogs
  * Live risk score with per-section breakdown
  * Hardware temperature (lm-sensors) and SMART drive health checks
  * Optional Timeshift snapshot before destructive actions
  * Multi-language UI (12 languages including RTL Arabic)
  * Full undo / rollback log persisted across sessions
  * CVE lookup against the Ubuntu security tracker
  * Integration with Lynis, deborphan, smartmontools, lm-sensors
